    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/research/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>jaeho.lee@postech.ac.kr (Jaeho Lee)</author>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/research/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;research&#34;&gt;research&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; href=&#34;#research&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I prove theorems and design algorithms for machine learning.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;goals&#34;&gt;goals&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; href=&#34;#goals&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;My long-term goal is to make AI more &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;responsible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; &amp;mdash; accessible, sustainable, and righteous. I currently focus on &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;efficient ai&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;. In particular, I aim to characterize the fundamental trade-offs among three factors:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;predictive performance&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;inference cost&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;training cost&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;While I prefer to keep my algorithms domain-agnostic, I enjoy working with data modalities where the efficiency is critical&amp;mdash;e.g., robotics or surgical imaging.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
